An 18-year-old student at a school in Finland went on the rampage Wednesday, shooting dead seven classmates and the headmistress and wounding a dozen others before turning his gun on himself.
The teenaged gunman who shot dead eight people at a Finnish school before turning his gun on himself was carrying 500 bullets and fired at least 69, police said on Thursday.
An 18-year-old man opened fire at a high school in southern Finland on Wednesday, leaving at least seven people dead and 11 injured, officials said.
Eight victims of the Finnish school shooting have been identified, including the school's principal and nurse as well as six students, Finish police confirmed on Thursday.
